        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 2 at 5:02PM EDT until May 2 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles southeast
of Meadowood, or 6 miles southeast of Butler, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Kittanning, Ford City, Meadowood, Oak Hills, West Kittanning,
Saxonburg, Worthington, West Hills, Manorville, Ford Cliff,
Applewold and Lenape Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.</instruction>
